  "notes": "Western Aragonese (Jacetania, Cinco Villas). Transitional to Castilian: strongest Castilian phonological influence among Aragonese dialects. Palatal lateral /ʎ/ lost to /ʝ/ (yeísmo). Vowel system reduced to five vowels (Castilian pattern). Latin J- → [x] (Castilian pattern) rather than Aragonese [tʃ] or [dʒ]. Fewer distinctive Aragonese features than Eastern or Central varieties.",
